SIMPLE: ovate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ovate
<hw>O"vate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>ovatus</ets>,
from <ets>ovum</ets> egg. See <er>Oval</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Shaped like an egg, with the lower extremity
broadest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having the shape of an egg, or of
the longitudinal section of an egg, with the broader end basal.</def>
<rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ovate-acuminate</ent>⟦br⟧
